-- Hungarian Far-Right Party Leader Istvan Csurka Dies, MTI Reports
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-02-04T11:56:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-04/hungarian-far-right-party-leader-istvan-csurka-dies-mti-reports.html
Istvan Csurka, leader of the
Hungarian far-right MIEP party, has died at the age of 77,
state-run news service  MTI  reported.  Csurka, a playwright and newspaper editor, served in
parliament between 1998 and 2002. MIEP, which is no longer
represented in parliament, has been replaced by Jobbik as the
most popular radical nationalist party in  Hungary .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  